<li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation news cs1">"Vienna Celebrates 'the Most Influential Rabbi of Modern History'<span class="cs1-kern-right"></span>". Alexandria, VA. Connection Newspapers. May 7, 2014. <q>Chabad Tysons Jewish Center will present Paradigm Shift: Transformational Life Teachings of the Lubavitcher Rebbe, a new six-session course by the Rohr Jewish Learning Institute. The course will be offered as part of a series of local activities in Northern Virginia marking 20 years since the passing of "the Rebbe", Rabbi Menachem M. Schneerson of righteous memory. The Rebbe was a visionary religious leader who inspired countless individuals during his lifetime and established a global network of educational, social, and religious institutions to revive the post-holocaust Jewish landscape.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Vienna+Celebrates+%27the+Most+Influential+Rabbi+of+Modern+History%27&amp;rft.date=2014-05-07&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARebbe" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
